{"title_page": "K\u00e4rstin Ehrnlund", "text_new": "{{short description|Swedish golfer}}\n{{Infobox golfer\n| name              = K\u00e4rstin Ehrnlund\n| image             = \n| imagesize         = <!-- Optional, default is 200px -->\n| caption           = \n| fullname          = \t\n| nickname          = \n| birth_date        = {{birth date and age|1959|2|10|df=y}}\n| birth_place       = [[Karlstad]], [[Sweden]]\n| death_date        = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|1959|2|10|df=y}} -->\n| death_place       = \n| height            = \n| weight            = \n| nationality       = {{SWE}}\n| residence         = [[Gothenburg]], [[Sweden]]\n| spouse            = \n| partner           = \n| children          = \n| college           = \n| yearpro           = 1979\n| retired           = \n| tour              = \n| extour            = [[Ladies European Tour]]\n| prowins           = 2\n| letwins           = 2\n| otherwins         = \n| majorwins         = <!-- Number of Major Championship wins -->\n| nabisco           = \n| lpga              = \n| wusopen           = \n| wbritopen         = \n| evian             = \n| wghofid           = <!-- World Golf Hall of Fame member ID -->\n| wghofyear         = <!-- World Golf Hall of Fame year inducted -->\n| award1            = <!-- Achievement or award details -->\n| year1             = <!-- Year(s) of achievement or award -->\n| award2            = \n| year2             = \n| awardssection     = <!-- location of awards page or section -->\n}}\n'''K\u00e4rstin Ehrnlund''' (born 10 February 1959 in [[Karlstad]]) is a [[List of Swedish professional golfers|Swedish professional golfer]].\n\nEhrnlund was a pioneer of professional golf in Sweden. She was the first Swedish woman to join a [[professional golf tours|professional golf tour]] and the first Swede to record a victory on an international tour. After winning the Swedish Match-play Championship in 1977 and 1978, she turned professional on the nascent Women's Professional Golf Association (WPGA) Tour, later renamed [[Ladies European Tour]]. In August 1980 Ehrnlund played the Welsh Classic at [[Whitchurch Golf Club]] in [[Cardiff]]. She was in the lead after two rounds with 68\u201374, and after the last round was cancelled due to rain she was declared the winner. Four years later she won another Ladies European Tour title, the United Friendly Tournament at two-time [[Ryder Cup]]-venue [[Southport and Ainsdale Golf Club]] near [[Liverpool]].<ref>[http://svenskagolfmuseet.se/golfens-profiler/ Golf Profiles], Swedish Golf Museum, accessed 17 November 2016 {{in lang|sv}}</ref> [[Ove Sellberg]] became the first Swede to record a victory on the [[European Tour]] in 1986.\n\n==Amateur wins==\n*1977 Swedish Match-play Championship\n*1978 Swedish Match-play Championship, Swedish International Stroke-play Championship, German Open Amateur Championship, Austrian Open Amateur Championship\n\nSource:<ref>[http://www.svenskgolf.se/artiklar/folja/20120816/har-ar-alla-vinnare-i-sm-match SM Match Winners], Swedish Golf, accessed 17 November 2016 {{in lang|sv}}</ref><ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Professional wins (2)==\n===Ladies European Tour (2)===\n*1980 McEwans Lager Welsh Classic\n*1984 United Friendly Tournament\n\nSource:<ref>[http://www.golf.se/globalassets/tavling/blagula-segrar/alla-svenska-segrar.pdf Swedish Professional Tour Victories], Swedish Golf Association, accessed 17 November 2016 {{in lang|sv}}</ref>\n\n==Team appearances==\n'''Amateur'''\n*[[Espirito Santo Trophy]] (representing Sweden): 1978<ref name=\":0\">{{citeweb |url=http://www.e-magin.se/paper/1pfc350j/popup/1? |title=Golf - Den Stora Sporten' |language=Swedish |trans-title=Golf - the Great Sport |publisher=Swedish Golf Federation 100 Years |pages=184, 209, 220, 221}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Golfdata|11175}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ehrnlund, Karstin}}\n[[Category:Swedish female golfers]]\n[[Category:Ladies European Tour golfers]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Karlstad]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Gothenburg]]\n[[Category:1959 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Swedish golfer}}\n{{Infobox golfer\n| name              = K\u00e4rstin Ehrnlund\n| image             = \n| imagesize         = <!-- Optional, default is 200px -->\n| caption           = \n| fullname          = \t\n| nickname          = \n| birth_date        = {{birth date and age|1959|2|10|df=y}}\n| birth_place       = [[Karlstad]], [[Sweden]]\n| death_date        = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|1959|2|10|df=y}} -->\n| death_place       = \n| height            = \n| weight            = \n| nationality       = {{SWE}}\n| residence         = [[Gothenburg]], [[Sweden]]\n| spouse            = \n| partner           = \n| children          = \n| college           = \n| yearpro           = 1979\n| retired           = \n| tour              = \n| extour            = [[Ladies European Tour]]\n| prowins           = 2\n| letwins           = 2\n| otherwins         = \n| majorwins         = <!-- Number of Major Championship wins -->\n| nabisco           = \n| lpga              = \n| wusopen           = \n| wbritopen         = \n| evian             = \n| wghofid           = <!-- World Golf Hall of Fame member ID -->\n| wghofyear         = <!-- World Golf Hall of Fame year inducted -->\n| award1            = <!-- Achievement or award details -->\n| year1             = <!-- Year(s) of achievement or award -->\n| award2            = \n| year2             = \n| awardssection     = <!-- location of awards page or section -->\n}}\n'''K\u00e4rstin Ehrnlund''' (born 10 February 1959 in [[Karlstad]]) is a [[List of Swedish professional golfers|Swedish professional golfer]].\n\nEhrnlund was a pioneer of professional golf in Sweden. She was the first Swedish woman to join a [[professional golf tours|professional golf tour]] and the first Swede to record a victory on an international tour. After winning the Swedish Championship in 1977 and 1978 she turned professional on the nascent Women's Professional Golf Association (WPGA) Tour, later renamed [[Ladies European Tour]]. In August 1980 Ehrnlund played the Welsh Classic at [[Whitchurch Golf Club]] in [[Cardiff]]. She was in the lead after two rounds with 68\u201374, and after the last round was cancelled due to rain she was declared the winner. Four years later she won another Ladies European Tour title, the United Friendly Tournament at two-time [[Ryder Cup]]-venue [[Southport and Ainsdale Golf Club]] near [[Liverpool]].<ref>[http://svenskagolfmuseet.se/golfens-profiler/ Golf Profiles], Swedish Golf Museum, accessed 17 November 2016 {{in lang|sv}}</ref> [[Ove Sellberg]] became the first Swede to record a victory on the [[European Tour]] in 1986.\n\n==Amateur wins==\n*1977 Swedish Match-play Championship\n*1978 Swedish Match-play Championship, Swedish International Stroke-play Championship, German Open Amateur Championship, Austrian Open Amateur Championship\n\nSource:<ref>[http://www.svenskgolf.se/artiklar/folja/20120816/har-ar-alla-vinnare-i-sm-match SM Match Winners], Swedish Golf, accessed 17 November 2016 {{in lang|sv}}</ref><ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Professional wins (2)==\n===Ladies European Tour (2)===\n*1980 McEwans Lager Welsh Classic\n*1984 United Friendly Tournament\n\nSource:<ref>[http://www.golf.se/globalassets/tavling/blagula-segrar/alla-svenska-segrar.pdf Swedish Professional Tour Victories], Swedish Golf Association, accessed 17 November 2016 {{in lang|sv}}</ref>\n\n==Team appearances==\n'''Amateur'''\n*[[Espirito Santo Trophy]] (representing Sweden): 1978<ref name=\":0\">{{citeweb |url=http://www.e-magin.se/paper/1pfc350j/popup/1? |title=Golf - Den Stora Sporten' |language=Swedish |trans-title=Golf - the Great Sport |publisher=Swedish Golf Federation 100 Years |pages=184, 209, 220, 221}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Golfdata|11175}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ehrnlund, Karstin}}\n[[Category:Swedish 